@gjacoby126 
Yes, you are right in that the getController method cannot be refactored to use a common interface since MetadataRpcController and ServerRpcController use shaded and unshaded interfaces respectively, and casting leads to compile time errors.

As I understand puts and queries on the SYSTEM CATALOG table use the default handler pool. MetadataRpcController is used only for the MetdataService methods.

And we can put this method:
```
    @Override
    public Optional getRegionObserver() {
        return Optional.of(this);
    }

```

> @jpisaac @tkhurana - could you please explain what's different between this version of 6751 and the one that was previously committed and then reverted?

@gjacoby126 The difference is the use of biginteger to avoid overflow issues when determining whether to use skip scan or range scan. 
https://github.com/apache/phoenix/pull/1495/files#diff-9494157265dca11f05041f6a7238b64857cc22e08c3c23e92412e1a0da1d12feR335-R343

> @chrajeshbabu - looks like there are test failures in PhoenixTableLevelMetricsIT -- do the tests need to be updated with different metric values to assert on now that the query planning is more efficient in some cases?

Since we are not calling get table regions API here custom connection queries don't have effect and ignored the tests.
@gjacoby126
